The @Query annotation in Spring Data JPA is used to define custom queries.
using JPQL (Java Persistence Query Language) or native SQL.
This annotation allows you to write complex queries and perform operations that may not be possible with standard method naming conventions.

In the applications.yml
spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=update
spring.jpa.show-sql=true

Create the Repository Interface
define custom queries using the @Query annotation.

